The crisis rocking the All Progressives Congress (APC) has taken a new dimension following rumours of Akpanudoedehe’s resignation, Akpanudoedehe, the National Secretary of the PDP Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC), was reported to have been forced to resign by the committee. Sources claimed the President directed the CECPC secretary’s resignation but DAILY POST investigation showed there has not been any official statement to that effect.